        "goal_understanding": "The goal is to navigate a grid-based puzzle, matching your carried piece's shape, color, and rotation to the requirements of goal cells by stepping on modifier tiles, then moving onto those goals to complete them. Completing all goals advances you to the next level, with the ultimate aim of finishing all levels.",
        "mechanics_understanding": "The game operates on a 2D grid where you move in four cardinal directions (north, south, east, west). Each move costs 1 stamina; running out of stamina costs a life and refills stamina. Losing all lives ends the game. Walls block movement (indicated by 'blocked_directions'). Modifier tiles alter your piece: shape modifiers cycle through 6 shapes, color modifiers cycle orange\u2192blue\u2192green\u2192red\u2192orange, and rotation modifiers rotate the piece 90\u00b0 clockwise (0\u00b0\u219290\u00b0\u2192180\u00b0\u2192270\u00b0\u21920\u00b0). A goal cell is activated only when your piece's shape, color, and rotation all match its requirements. Stepping on an activated goal completes it. You must plan routes efficiently, avoiding blocked paths and using modifiers to achieve the needed piece state."
